<p>The tone and length of your message should reflect your relationship with the deceased and the recipient.  Keep it concise and sincere, focusing on expressing your heartfelt sympathy and offering your support. Avoid lengthy explanations or unsolicited advice.  Simply conveying your sorrow and offering comfort is often the most impactful approach. Remember to tailor your message to the specific situation and your relationship with the grieving party.</p>
    

